Here's how to create a simple rigid body node in Godot Engine 3 and 4 using the GDscript script language and transfer the same script to Godot Engine 4:

In Godot Engine 3:

1. Create a new project and add the GDscript package to your project settings.
2. Create a new script called "MyRigidBodyNode.gd" and paste the following code into it:

```gd
class MyRigidBodyNode extends KinematicBodyNode {
    private RigidBody body;

    void _PhysicsProcess(float deltaTime) {
        body.SetPosition(body.GetPosition() + deltaTime * Vector3.forward);
    }
}
```

3. Save and run the script to see it in action.

In Godot Engine 4:

1. Create a new project and add the GDscript package to your project settings.
2. Create a new script called "MyRigidBodyNode.gd" and paste the following code into it:

```gd
class MyRigidBodyNode extends KinematicBodyNode {
    private RigidBody body;

    void _PhysicsProcess(float deltaTime) {
        body.SetPosition(body.GetPosition() + Vector3.forward(deltaTime));
    }
}
```

3. Save and run the script to see it in action.

